<m1><styl>txt,14p<ql>
<styl>crline <m0>From Herald Staff and Wire Reports<ep>
<m1><ep>
<m0>  Certified Vacations said chief executive Michael F. Stone has quit, and the Fort Lauderdale-based tour operator will be run by an Alamo Rent-A-Car executive until a replacement is found. Alamo Chairman Mike Egan owns the large travel company.<ep>
   After four years as president, Stone, 46, is leaving ``to pursue several new opportunities,'' according to a statement from Egan. Alamo's vice chairman and chief operating officer Roger Ballou, a travel industry veteran, will temporarily manage the company.<ep>
   Certified, which cut 42 people from its work force in January, employs more than 800 people in Fort Lauderdale and 90 in Salt Lake City.<ql>
