<m4>   LINE 1 IS 3.08 PICA(S) SHORT<m2><ql>
<m0>SEC over disclosures<ql>
<m1><ue5><m4>   LINE 2 IS 1.51 PICA(S) SHORT<m2><ql>
<m4>   TOTAL HEAD DEPTH IS .608 INCHES<m2><ql>
<ql>
<m1><styl>txt,14p<ql>
<ep>
<m0>  Royce Laboratories and its chairman reached a settlement with the Securities and Exchange Commission in connection with an investigation into possible violations of federal securities laws.<ep>
   Royce Labs is a Miami-based maker of generic drugs. The SEC investigation focused on disclosures made by the company between July 1991 and April 1992 regarding the status of its abbreviated new drug applications for Piroxicam and Minoxidil. The probe also concerned sales of Royce Labs' securities.<ep>
   Chairman Patrick J. McEnany agreed to pay a $25,000 administrative fine to defray some of the SEC's expenses for the investigation. McEnany and Royce also agreed to a civil injunction requiring them to comply with federal securities laws in the future, though they neither admitted nor denied a violation had occurred.<ql>
