<m1><styl>txt,14p<ql>
<ep>
<m0>  Alamo Rent-a-Car is looking for off-airport property in Calgary and Toronto to double the number of its rental sites in Canada over the next 12 to 18 months. Fort Lauderdale-based Alamo, the third largest rental car company in the United States, said it also is considering expanding to Edmonton, Winnipeg, Ottawa and Quebec City.<ep>
   Alamo operates two on-airport rental sites in Montreal and Vancouver. Budget and Tilden are the two largest rental companies in Canada, each with about 400 locations, according to the Canadian Car and Truck Rental Association.<ep>
